```javascript
return { event_type: data.event_type, user_id: data.data.user.id, user_email: data.data.user.email };
```

This will take an input like:
```json
{
  "event_type": "user_created",
  "data": {
    "user": {
      "id": "123",
      "email": "test@example.com"
    }
  }
}
```

And produce:
```json
{
  "event_type": "user_created",
  "user_id": "123",
  "user_email": "test@example.com"
}
```

This matches the acceptance criteria. The `data` object is not included in the output, and `user_id` and `user_email` are at the root level.

